# cost factor 

1. industrial robots
avg cost 
- $50,000 - $100,000 for a basic robot
- $150,000 - $200,000 for more advanced models
- $500,000 or more for highly specialized robots

2. collaborative robots (cobots)
avg cost
- $20,000 - $50,000 for basic cobots
- $50,000 - $100,000 for more advanced cobots
- $100,000 or more for highly specialized cobots

3. autonomous mobile robots (AMRs)
avg cost
- $10,000 - $50,000 for basic AMRs
- $50,000 - $100,000 for more advanced AMRs
- $100,000 or more for highly specialized AMRs

4. robotic process automation (RPA) software
avg cost
- $5,000 - $20,000 per bot for basic RPA software
- $20,000 - $50,000 per bot for more advanced RPA software
- $50,000 or more per bot for highly specialized RPA software

5. maintenance and support costs
- annual maintenance costs can range from 10% to 20% of the initial cost of
the robot or software
- support costs can vary depending on the level of support required and the
 complexity of the robot or software, but can range from a few thousand dollars to tens
  of thousands of dollars per year.


