1.compensation time- The time it takes for a robot to complete a task can vary greatly 
depending on the complexity of the task and the capabilities of the robot.

time = approx 2 years ( on the basis of productivity and efficiency of the robot)

2. return on investment (ROI) - The ROI of a robot can vary greatly depending on the cost of the robot, 
the productivity gains it provides, and the cost savings it generates.
ROI = (Productivity Gains + Cost Savings) / Cost of the Robot
3. payback period - The payback period is the time it takes for the cost savings
 generated by the robot to equal the initial cost of the robot.
Payback Period = Cost of the Robot / Annual Cost Savings
